data.chText: 就职的；开幕的；成立的；创始的

before.enText: of an official speech, meeting, etc.

data.enText: first, and marking the beginning of sth important, for example the time when a new leader or parliament starts work, when a new organization is formed or when sth is used for the first time
the inaugural meeting of the geographical society
the inaugural flight of the space shuttle

simple_means.memory_skill: in 进入 + aug 增加 + ural → 进入〔人数〕增多的 → 开幕的

tr: the ceremonial induction into a position
example: the new president obviously enjoyed his inauguration

tr: an address delivered at an inaugural ceremony (especially by a United States president)

example: the initiative phase in the negotiations
an initiatory step toward a treaty
his first (or maiden) speech in Congress

tr: occurring at or characteristic of a formal investiture or induction

value.def: An inaugural meeting or speech is the first meeting of a new organization or the first speech by the new leader of an organization or a country.

example.ex: In his inaugural address, the President appealed for unity.
example.tran: 总统在他的就职演说中呼吁国家统一。

partsOfSpeech.dec: auc 增加 + tion 表名词 →〔价钱〕增加 → 拍卖
auc 增加 + tion 表名词 + eer 表专做某种工作或从事某种职业的人 → 拍卖商
aug 增加 + ment 智力 → 增大

partsOfSpeech.d: 八月（八月是水果成熟的季节）

partsOfSpeech.dec: aug 增加 + ust → 威严不断增加 → 威严的
in 进入 + aug 增加 + ural → 进入〔人数〕增多的 → 开幕的
in 进入 + aug 增加 + urate → 进入增加 → 开始
